This paper is likely to belong to the sub-category of cs.LG (Machine Learning) as it proposes a new method for unsupervised domain adaptation based on moment matching. It also involves learning discriminative representations in the target domain, which is a common task in machine learning. 

It is also likely to belong to cs.CV (Computer Vision) as domain adaptation is a common problem in computer vision, and the proposed method is evaluated on several computer vision datasets. 

cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) is another likely sub-category as the proposed method involves learning representations that can generalize to different domains, which is a common task in AI. 

cs.CL (Computation and Language) is less likely but still possible as the proposed method involves matching higher-order statistics, which can be relevant in natural language processing tasks. 

cs.MM (Multimedia) is also less likely but possible as the proposed method is evaluated on several multimedia datasets, such as image classification and object detection.
